CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1945, pg. 8, reads: "Student Aid Committee Gathers - A fine group of public-spirited citizens met Monday night at Kay Boys Club to assist in working out plans for the mammoth card party to be given June 14 at the YMHA, to benefit the Student Aid Committee of the Urban League....Far right: Mrs. Thomas Barton accepting ticket money from W.P. Young and Mrs. Wynona Graves, both of whom reported substantially that night... - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Thomas Barton accepting ticket money for card party benefit from W. P. Young and Wynona Graves, in Kay Boys Club
